      "lernziele": "<p>Students will be able to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>explain the purpose and the typical use cases for modern cryptographic primitives,</li>\n<li>identify common issues when applying or implementing cryptographic primitives. For example, the use of weak randomness generators, or padding oracle attacks</li>\n<li>recognize the importance of cryptographic agility at the example of post-quantum cryptography</li>\n</ul>",
      "planinhalt": "<ul>\n<li>Randomness Generation, PRNG, PRF</li>\n<li>Cryptographic Security</li>\n<li>Block &amp; Stream Ciphers</li>\n<li>Hash Functions</li>\n<li>HMAC, CMAC</li>\n<li>Signature schemes</li>\n<li>Key Exchange</li>\n<li>Post-quantum cryptography</li>\n<li>(Topic of the Year: E.g. zero-knowledge proofs)</li>\n</ul>",
